---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout currentPath="/about">
	<section class="section">
		<div class="section-header">
			<span class="section-label">About Me</span>
			<h1 class="page-title">Game development is where creativity, systems, and player experience meet.</h1>
			<p class="lead">I am a game developer with a strong background in interactive systems, design pipelines, and polished playable experiences. I build with player-first thinking and a focus on making work that feels confident, expressive, and memorable.</p>
		</div>

		<div class="highlight-grid">
			<div class="highlight-panel">
				<h2>My journey</h2>
				<p class="card-text">I started in game design, moved into engine systems, and now build end-to-end projects that blend gameplay, narrative, and technical polish. My work includes commercial games, research-driven thesis systems, and architecture-inspired interactive experiences.</p>
				<ul class="feature-list">
					<li class="feature-item"><h3>Player-first systems</h3><p>Create responsive mechanics that feel good to play and are easy to iterate.</p></li>
					<li class="feature-item"><h3>Technical craftsmanship</h3><p>Ship game logic, tools, and level frameworks with strong architecture and quality-first mindset.</p></li>
					<li class="feature-item"><h3>Collaborative production</h3><p>Work closely with artists, designers, and producers to deliver polished milestones on schedule.</p></li>
				</ul>
			</div>

			<div class="highlight-panel">
				<h2>What I bring</h2>
				<ul class="feature-list">
					<li class="feature-item"><strong>Design systems</strong><span>Gameplay prototypes, progression loops, balance tuning.</span></li>
					<li class="feature-item"><strong>Game tech</strong><span>Blueprints, C#, Unreal/Unity workflows, version control.</span></li>
					<li class="feature-item"><strong>Production focus</strong><span>Clear communication, milestone delivery, and creative problem-solving.</span></li>
				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<section class="section">
		<div class="section-header">
			<span class="section-label">Skills + mindset</span>
			<h2>Why I’m a strong candidate for game studios and interactive teams.</h2>
		</div>

		<div class="grid-split">
			<div class="card">
				<h3 class="card-title">Creative systems</h3>
				<p class="card-text">I develop core systems that support player choice, emergent gameplay, and meaningful reward loops. My work is built to be fun, balanced, and easy to tune.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<h3 class="card-title">Production-ready delivery</h3>
				<p class="card-text">I prioritize clean implementation, documentation, and handoff so teams can move quickly without compromising quality.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<h3 class="card-title">Cross-disciplinary collaboration</h3>
				<p class="card-text">I communicate clearly with designers, artists, and engineers to keep scope realistic and deliver on shared creative goals.</p>
			</div>
			<div class="card">
				<h3 class="card-title">Player empathy</h3>
				<p class="card-text">From onboarding to endgame, I center player experience in every interaction, interface, and moment of feedback.</p>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
